tafsir[2]{c,v,t}:
  1,1,"In the name of Allah, the Most Gracious, the Most Merciful.\n\nThis is the first verse of Surah Al-Fatiha. The Basmalah is recommended at the beginning of every good deed. Imam Ibn Kathir said: \"In the name of Allah\" means: I begin with every name of Allah, because the word \"name\" is singular and added, so it includes all the beautiful names. \"Allah\" is the One worthy of worship, deserving of being singled out for worship due to His attributes of divinity which are attributes of perfection. \"The Most Gracious, the Most Merciful\" are two names indicating that He possesses vast and great mercy that encompasses everything."
  1,4,"(The Beneficent) the Gentle. (The Merciful) the Gentle."
